author: commercialappeal.com
title: Oct. 1 Dandy Dozen Debate results
text:
The Dandy Dozen Debate is a chance for fans to pick their own top 12 prep football teams from the Shelby-Metro area. While John Varlas' version of the Dandy Dozen remains the "official" one, we'll give you the opportunity to make your own picks each week and see how it matches up against his poll.
Here are the results for the fan vote held Sept. 30-Oct. 1:
1. Northpoint (6-0) (111 first-place votes)
2. Ridgeway (4-2) (39)
3. Whitehaven (5-1) (81)
4. CBHS (4-1) (44)
5. White Station (4-2) (68)
6. Arlington (4-2) (4)
7. Southwind (4-1)
8. MUS (4-2) (2)
9. Munford (5-0) (16)
10. Cordova (6-0) (20)
11. Olive Branch (3-2) (28)
12. East (4-1) (2)
Below is John Varlas' Dandy Dozen:
1. Whitehaven (5-1)
2. East (4-1)
3. CBHS (4-1)
4. White Station (4-2)
5. Cordova (6-0)
6. MUS (4-2)
7. Munford (5-0)
8. DeSoto Central (4-2)
9. Southwind (4-1)
10. Ridgeway (4-2)
11. Arlington (4-2)
12. Northpoint (6-0)
Dropped out: Hernando
